  "text": "Why do you unlock your phone 144 times a day? Explained by Koala. That's once every six minutes. You're not deciding. Your hand is. By lunch, you've already pulled the phone out 60 times for nothing. Koala used to do the same. Unlock. Scroll. Sleep. Unlock again. Felt like the phone was running Koala, not the other way around. Then Koala figured it out. Your brain isn't addicted to your phone. It's addicted to dopamine. The unlock is a reflex. is chasing chemistry. So don't fight the reflex. Give it somewhere else to land. Running. Drawing. Lifting. Anything that ends in a result you can see. Then film yourself doing it. Time lapse it. Same reach. Better payoff. Koala doesn't gatekeep. Koala used lock-in club to track his productivity using time lapses.",
